# todostodo — Project Overview

ASP.NET Core Web API + React frontend. Key stack:
- **ORM**: Entity Framework Core with SQLite
- **Auth**: ASP.NET Core Identity + JWT bearer tokens
- **Validation**: FluentValidation
- **Models**: `Entry` (base), `ToDo : Entry`, `Settings`; all scoped to `ApplicationUser`

Before running locally:
```
dotnet user-secrets set JWT:Key "your-key"
dotnet ef database update
```

## Example: correct model ownership pattern
```csharp
// ✅ Always scope queries to the authenticated user
var userId = User.FindFirstValue(ClaimTypes.NameIdentifier);
var items = await _db.ToDos.Where(t => t.ApplicationUserId == userId).ToListAsync();

// ❌ Never return unscoped data
var items = await _db.ToDos.ToListAsync();
```

## Example: consistent status values
```csharp
// ✅ Use the Status field values established in Entry
public string Status { get; set; } = "active"; // "active" | "inactive"

// ❌ Don't invent new status strings inline
item.Status = "done"; // not a valid status
```
